# NextOS picodrive — gamepad → keyboard (workaround p/ sdl12-compat bug
# que descarta SDL_JOYBUTTONDOWN events. PicoDrive le SDL keys diretamente.)
# SNES-style USB Gamepad layout:
#   button0 (top-right/X)    → 'a' gptokeyb → c (PicoDrive C)
#   button1 (bot-right/A)    → 'b' gptokeyb → x (PicoDrive B)
#   button2 (bot-left/B)     → 'x' gptokeyb → z (PicoDrive A)
#   button3 (top-left/Y)     → 'y' gptokeyb → escape (Menu PicoDrive)
a = c
b = x
x = z
y = esc
back = esc
start = enter
guide = enter
l1 = a
l2 = q
r1 = s
r2 = w
up = up
down = down
left = left
right = right
left_analog_up = up
left_analog_down = down
left_analog_left = left
left_analog_right = right
